FOWLER A MAJOR FORCE

He may be ranked 18 in the world, but Rickie Fowler’s form in majors this year reads tied fifth, tied second and tied second. 

Fowler had an excellent start yesterday with a 69 and if he holds his place until Sunday, he would be the first to finish in the top five of all four majors in a year since Tiger Woods in 2005.

