CROWD PLEASER WATSON

Tiger had them growling and there were plenty of roars for Rory but one of the warmest welcomes from the gallery was for Ryder Cup captain Tom Watson at the first hole. 

The 64-year-old, whose best finish in the US PGA was second in 1978, responded by splitting the fairway with his drive — which led to even greater cheers.

